properties.areaDesc: North Snowy Range Foothills; Central Carbon County
properties.headline: Blizzard Warning issued January 1 at 9:24AM MST until January 1 at 11:00PM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
...Winter Storm Warning Through Thursday Afternoon for the Snowy
and Sierra Madre Ranges...

...Blizzard Warning for Carbon County from Arlington to Rawlins
Through This Evening...

* WHAT...Blizzard conditions. Additional snow accumulations of up
to 4 inches. Winds gusting as high as 65 mph.

* WHERE...Interstate 80 Corridor from Arlington to Rawlins.

* WHEN...Until 11 PM MST this evening.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. Patchy blowing
snow could significantly reduce visibility. The hazardous
conditions could impact the evening commute. Strong winds
could cause tree damage.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...If caught in these blizzard conditions in
your vehicle...stay with your vehicle. Trying to walk to safety
will lead to you becoming lost in whiteout conditions.
properties.instruction:
Travel should be restricted to emergencies only. If you must
travel, have a winter survival kit with you. If you get stranded,
stay with your vehicle.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: BLIZZARD WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL 11 PM MST THIS EVENING
